article.headline: Long Island U. 76, Bryant 61
article.story: NEW YORK -- Kyle Johnson scored 19 points to lead Long Island University to a 76-61 victory over Bryant on Wednesday night. Jaytornah Wisseh added 15 points for the Blackbirds (7-7), while Mike Culpo added 12 and Julian Boyd had 11 points and 11 rebounds. Peter Lambert led Bryant (2-12) with 18 points and Nick Pontes had 10. Long Island scored the last six points of the first half and the first nine of the second to take a 38-25 lead on a jumper by Johnson with 17:52 to play. The Bulldogs, in their first season of a four-year transition into Division I, snapped a nine-game losing streak in their last game with a victory over Yale.
